==English==

===Etymology 1===
Either from {{inh|en|enm|abbreviaten}}, from {{der|en|la|abbreviātus}}, perfect passive participle of {{m|la|abbreviō||to shorten}}, formed from {{m|la|ad}} + {{m|la|breviō||shorten}}, from {{m|la|brevis||short}} or {{back-form|en|abbreviation|nocap=1}}.<ref>{{R:CDOE|page=2}}</ref> {{doublet|en|abridge}}.

====Pronunciation====
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|en|/ə.ˈbɹiː.vi.eɪt/}}
* {{a|GenAm}} {{IPA|en|/əˈbɹi.vi.eɪt/}}
* {{audio|en|en-us-abbreviate.ogg|Audio (US)}}

====Verb====
{{en-verb}}

# {{lb|en|obsolete|transitive}} To shorten by omitting parts or details. {{defdate|Attested from around (1350 to 1470) until the late 17<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED>{{R:SOED5|page=3}}</ref>
#* {{quote-book|en|title=Essays|author={{w|Francis Bacon}}|year=1597|passage=It is one thing to '''abbreviate''' by contracting, another by cutting off.}}
# {{lb|en|obsolete|intransitive}} To speak or write in a brief manner. {{defdate|Attested from the late 16<sup>th</sup> century until the early 17<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To make [[short]]er; to [[shorten]] (in time); to [[abridge]]; to shorten by ending sooner than planned. {{defdate|First attested from around (1350 to 1470).}}<ref name=SOED/>
#* {{quote-journal|en
|title=How our home delivery habit reshaped the world|author=Samanth Subramanian|date=November 21 2019|journal=The Guardian|url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2019/nov/21/how-our-home-delivery-habit-reshaped-the-world
|passage=But as delivery schedules have dwindled into hours, even the gigantic warehouse full of stuff in a central place such as the triangle is proving insufficient. Now, companies also need smaller distribution centres around the country, to respond rapidly to orders and to '''abbreviate''' the last mile as much as possible.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To reduce a word or phrase by means of [[contraction]] or [[omission]] to a shorter recognizable form. {{defdate|First attested in the late 16<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
#: {{ux|en|[[bovine spongiform encephalopathy]] is more commonly known by its '''abbreviated''' form ''BSE''.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive|mathematics}} To [[reduce]] to lower terms, as a [[fraction]].

